## 8. Why NCCL Works When Your Code Doesn't

NVIDIA's NCCL and its transport plugins handle all of the above internally:

- They enumerate ports correctly and test connectivity before selecting
- They force RoCEv2 GID selection
- They pre-resolve addresses through the driver, bypassing kernel ARP
- They have dual-path routing that works around broken links automatically
- They retry with exponential backoff and multiple QP creation strategies

This is not documentation NVIDIA publishes. We reverse-engineered it by comparing working NCCL connections against our failing ones, field-by-field, over several days.

Open standards shouldn't require proprietary knowledge to function correctly.

